<h2>Computer Science 418: 
<br> Computer Graphics <br>
Laboratory Exercises<br></h2>
<br clear=left>
<hr>

This is the Web Site for the Cornell University
undergraduate computer graphics laboratory, CS 418. 
These pages contain all of the materials for CS 418 including
 lab procedures, software and student results.
<p>

CS 418 is the lab section for 
<a href="http://www.tc.cornell.edu/Visualization/Education/cs417/"> 
CS 417 </a>
which deals with computer
graphics and scientific visualization at the level of <I>Computer
Graphics: Principles and Practice</I> by Foley et.al., or <I>3D
Computer Graphics</I> by Watt.  CS 418 is currently taught by <A HREF="http://www.tc.cornell.edu/~bruce/">Bruce
Land</A>, who is also the Project Leader for the Visualization Group at
the Cornell Theory Center.
<p>
<center>
These pages won first place in the <br> 1996 ACM SIGUCCS <br> Web-based
Education and Training materials competition.
</center>

